    <note>Wang(2) Kuang [10043] Author of the medical text cited as Ji shi quan sheng zhi mi fang, 4 ch. in the YLDD (SKTY, 103.9a [Vol. 3, p. 2104]; Ding Fubao, 489a-489b). In 1126, there were recommendations made that his talents were vast and he was given a title. In 1127, especially appointed to Chaofeng land and this seems to involve appontment to an actual office. (SHY:ZG, 62.8b). He was the son-in-law of the famous physician, Song Daofang [10044].From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:1127:  Appointed Chaofeng lang.陳松按：《宋人傳記資料索引(電子版)》從《宋史翼》記其名作「王況」，此據《宋以前醫籍考》、《古今醫統大全》等書作「王貺」。</note>
